{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4925b55-b4b8-439a-83c8-07d257a5622f","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**Short answer: No, you don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` anymore.**\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` talks to Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively (no VSTest bridge). That property was the opt-in for .NET 9 — it's now the default and can be removed.\n\nYour project is already correctly set up otherwise:\n- ✅ `EnableMSTestRunner` — builds the test project as an MTP executable\n- ✅ `OutputType: Exe` — required for the runner\n- ✅ `MSTest 3.8.0` — includes MTP support\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual and it will use MTP directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d78811ec-c415-4d94-b402-a9733b3070d7","outputTokens":175,"requestId":"982C:7D115:17D2EB:1F5AF7:69FFD8C6"},"id":"7110d242-ef69-4a87-af03-0f301ce61f8a","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:00:59.768Z","parentId":"db075bfd-522f-4af1-a6b4-424260b473ae"}
